## 2. What remains

It is worth being exact about what has, and has not, been done.

A great deal has been done. The framework now has more than a description of itself; it has operations. It can locate its own boundary and keep working at the edge of it. It can measure where it cannot prove. It can say what every created process must look like, and read those marks off a poem, a fugue, a painting, a body. It can account for how anything higher comes to be present in anything lower at all. These are not small results, and each was earned step by step, the way the section means them to be checked.

But notice where every one of them was performed. Each operation in this section took the structure itself for its object. The incompleteness result is the structure meeting its own limit. The truth measure rates proximity to the structure's own ground. The two laws are the structure's own grammar; the reading method recovers that grammar from things; even the three case studies, for all their variety, were chosen and read as confirmations that the method works — held up to the light, turned over, set down again. And the downward entry describes how the structure receives what enters it. We have spent the section indoors, learning every operation the house affords, and we have learned them well. We have not yet stepped outside.

This is not a shortfall to be apologized for. It is the proper order of the thing. One does not read the world before learning to read; one does not weigh history before holding the measure that weighs it. Everything here had to be settled first, and on its own terms, so that what comes next would have something to stand on. A completed room is not a smaller thing for opening onto a larger one. It is what makes the larger one enterable.

So the section closes with the instruments finished and idle, waiting for their proper work. What they are *for* is not the structure that produced them. It is the long, particular record of what has actually been made — the texts and the centuries, the traditions that did not know they were saying the same thing, the whole made world read at the scale it was made on. That reading is the next and the larger task, and the operations gathered here are exactly what it requires.

The wide reading is where we go now — out of the house at last, and gladly.

